reviews.text:
The malay lady wearing black scarf with black spectacles was  abit bias to customers. she can freaking smile and talk nicely to a male customer Infront of me, but when it was my turn to order, she took my order with an unhappy face. (I'm a lady by the way)

When she noticed that I look at her shirt for any name badge and look up at the stall name, she began to be more polite.

Ordered 6 curry puffs and paid for 6 curry puffs but the pack only had 5 curry puffs. Ordered 2 sweet potato but was given 2 small half size sweet potato. PLEASE CHECK BEFORE YOU LEAVE. I call it a SCAM.
Tau suan is the best. Dough stick is great 80% of the time. Though they were few occasions that it was really dense.

Horrible, bought the dao suan, come with  the you tiao already turned bad and black still let customers consume! obviously this is more than 1 overnight. So hard and dry! Come on, this is not free, we use money and buy, pls give what we have paid. If you don't waste your food and save costs then you will lost a customer. Will nv buy from them again!

I would like to praise this lady wearing black uniform with headscarf, her name was Amini, whom I bought my samosa, YouTiao,banana fritter,carrot cake. I would like to commemorate her customer service it was outstanding, very warmt, very friendly and even there's a queue, she's gone out her way to inform customer before me and myself there's discount 30cent for 4 item which I am not aware of if I go buy at other outlet. Will definitely return back here in future.
